r surname and shortened it to 羅 during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iv) from the name of one of the seven families from the Bandun Man, an ethnic group residing in ancient southwestern China (located mainly in present-day Sichuan province)."]}]},{"name":"River","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Rivers  .","Americanized form of some similar (like-sounding) surname in some other language, such as German <b>Riffer</b> (see   Riffey  ) and Spanish   Rivera  .","English: topographic name from a misdivision of Middle English <i>atter evere</i> ‘at the brow or edge’ (Old English <i>yfer</i>). The surname may denote someone who lived on the slope or brow of a hill, or someone who came from River in Tillington (Sussex), or perhaps River Hill (Binstead, Hants), which have the same etymology."],"variants":[{"name":"Rivers","meanings":["English: variant of   River  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","Americanized form (translation into English) of French <b>Larivière</b> (see   Lariviere  )."]},{"name":"Reaver","meanings":["English: occupational name or nickname from Middle English <i>revere</i> ‘reiver, robber’. This surname is very rare in Britain. Compare   River  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705188,"age":4,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":39,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris w